Ad Text:
About Proa Energy

Proa is heavily investing in expanding its energy management platform, delivering cutting-edge solutions for utility-scale renewable energy assets in Australia and around the world. Our multidisciplinary team of engineers, meteorologists, physicists, and IT specialists is rapidly expanding. We're currently seeking a Data Analytics Manager to lead our data scientists and analysts in designing and building advanced analytics solutions that drive the optimal operation of renewable energy assets.




About the Role

As the Data Analytics Manager, you will sit on the management team, reporting directly to the Managing Director, and lead the Data Analytics Team in delivering actionable insights and innovative solutions for utility-scale renewable assets. You will coordinate analytics activities across advanced modelling, software development, operations, and client management, ensuring that new products and R&D projects are deployed efficiently and at high quality. This is a unique opportunity to influence the future of energy management by building and deploying advanced analytics systems (forecasting, dispatch, bidding, data cleaning, ML, etc), supporting clients in optimizing their renewable energy assets, and engaging in “blue-sky” thinking about new products and solutions.




Key Responsibilities

Team Leadership – Manage a group of 8–10 data scientists and analysts, fostering a collaborative environment and delivering deep insights from the data generated by utility-scale renewable assets.

Expert Technical Advice – Guide R&D data science projects, brainstorming technical solutions and contributing to new product development.

Operational Analytics – Supervise and optimise the development, deployment, and monitoring processes of systems running operationally 24x7 for critical infrastructure.

Cross-team coordination – Work closely with product development, software, operations, and client management teams to ensure analytics solutions are integrated and deployed on time and to a high standard.

Regulatory Compliance – Understand market operator regulations and integrate them correctly into Proa’s systems.

Advanced modelling support – Develop and oversee advanced models in optimisation, forecasting, dispatch, data quality filtering, etc. for wide a variety of large scale renewable energy projects (solar, wind, batteries, hybrids, etc.).

System Architecture, Operation and Maintenance – Lead the architecture, operation and maintenance of  Proa’s analytics systems, ensuring processes remain robust, reliable, and scalable.




Skills and Experience

7+ years of experience leading technical teams.

Strong background in data science, algorithm design, machine learning, and physical science.

Experience working with cloud data environments, preferably Azure.

Proficiency in Python and MATLAB, or similar tools.

Strong problem-solving abilities and experience in software architecture and system design.

Excellent communication skills and the ability to lead, mentor, and motivate a technical team..




Desirable Skills

Knowledge of Australian energy regulations, particularly AEMO and NER rules.

Experience building optimisation systems for BESS and hybrid operations.

Experience running real-time operations for renewable energy plants.

On-site asset management and O&M operations experience at renewable energy plants.

Experience with advanced analytics, predictive modeling, or operational optimization in energy systems.




What We Offer

Competitive salary and benefits package.

Career growth and leadership development opportunities.

A collaborative, inclusive, and supportive work environment.

Flexible hybrid work arrangements.




Diversity and Inclusion

Proa Energy is proud to be a Work180 Endorsed Employer, dedicated to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace. We support work-life balance and encourage applications from individuals of all backgrounds, including women, culturally diverse candidates, and people with disabilities.




How to Apply

If you’re passionate about leading innovative software teams and contributing to the renewable energy sector, please send your resume and cover letter to careers@proa.energy with the subject “Data Analytics Manager Application.”

Applications open until the end of February 2026

Applicants must have legal rights to work in Australia.

Locations: Australia‑wide (with occasional travel to Canberra)

Term: 12 months + 2×12‑month extensions

Clearance: Ability to obtain Baseline

Ready to take charge of cloud cost optimisation across a major national organisation? We're searching for a Senior Cloud FinOps Specialist who can turn data into insight, spending into strategy, and cloud chaos into clarity.


You'll be the driving force behind smarter, leaner, value‑focused cloud operations. Working across finance, engineering, governance and product teams, you'll shape how the organisation manages cloud spend across AWS, Azure, GCP and M365. Your work will directly influence strategy, budgeting, accountability, and future cloud maturity.


Responsibilities:
Lead cloud cost optimisation across multiple platforms
Build and mature FinOps frameworks, governance and practices
Forecast, track and report on cloud spend
Partner with finance, engineering and governance teams to strengthen accountability
Produce dashboards, insights and leadership reports
Implement tooling and automation to streamline FinOps operations
Promote cloud financial awareness through training and advocacy
Continuously improve cloud financial management based on industry trends



Requirements
5+ years in cloud financial management or cloud operations
Strong knowledge of cloud billing models and cost structures
Experience across major cloud platforms
Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills
Strong analytical ability and financial modelling capability
Strategic mindset with the ability to influence change

About Us

At Agile Insights, we are passionate about empowering organisations to transform through the power of Data & AI. We work with global brands and leading organisations to deliver innovative solutions that solve real business challenges. We have a fantastic, long-standing relationship with Microsoft. We are extremely proud to be a Microsoft Solutions Specialist for four competencies including: Data Analytics and AI, Azure and Digital & App Innovation.

Your Role

As the Data Analytics Practice Manager, you will play a pivotal role in shaping and driving our analytics, consulting, and community engagement initiatives, with a focus on Microsoft Power BI and Fabric. You will lead a high-performing team of data analytics professionals, manage the creation of intellectual property (including accelerators and frameworks), support pre-sales activities and solutioning and ensure the successful delivery of technical solutions. You will also act as a trusted consultant to clients, while contributing to the wider data and analytics community through webinars, meetups, and seminars.

What You’ll Be Doing

Consulting & Technical Leadership

Work closely with clients to understand their business challenges and objectives, providing expert guidance and tailored analytics solutions.
Lead the development and implementation of advanced data analytics solutions using Microsoft Power BI, Fabric, Azure and related technologies.
Act as a trusted advisor, aligning technical solutions with business outcomes to deliver measurable impact.

Team & IP Management

Supervise, mentor, and support team members, fostering a culture of growth and collaboration.
Manage the P&L for your Practice, ensuring projects are running well, profitable and delivering high customer value.
Oversee the creation of accelerators, frameworks, and innovative IP to enhance our service offerings and improve delivery efficiency.
Provide hands-on technical guidance to the team while driving strategic initiatives.

Project Delivery & Pre-sales Support

Manage the technical delivery of projects, ensuring quality, timeliness, and alignment with client needs.
Partner with the sales team to contribute to proposals, estimates, and client presentations, demonstrating technical thought leadership.

Community Contribution

Plan, host, and participate in community engagement activities such as meetups, webinars, seminars, and technical workshops to showcase Agile Insights’ thought leadership in Data & AI.
Represent Agile Insights at industry conferences and events, building relationships and sharing insights on the latest trends and innovations in analytics.
Create content, such as blogs and presentations, to support the growth of the data analytics community and enhance Agile Insights’ brand presence.

What We’re Looking For

Proven experience in data analytics, with a strong focus on Microsoft Power BI and Microsoft Fabric.
Expertise in designing and implementing data analytics solutions, including dashboards, data models, and integration with Azure data platforms.
Consulting experience, with the ability to understand client challenges and deliver impactful solutions.
Demonstrated experience in managing and leading teams in a technical capacity.
Experience with whole of practice management: outcomes, capability, quality, timeliness, and value.
Ability to develop and manage reusable IP, such as accelerators and frameworks, that drive efficiency and innovation.
Excellent communication and presentation skills to effectively engage with clients, internal stakeholders, and the wider community.
Experience hosting or contributing to community events, such as webinars, meetups, or seminars, is highly desirable.
Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to address complex data challenges.

What’s In It for You?

At Agile Insights, we believe in nurturing talent and creating a supportive, flexible, and rewarding workplace. Here’s what you can look forward to:

Wellbeing: Access to hybrid work arrangements, an Employee Assistance Program, and an individualised gym and wellbeing program.
Flexibility: Work from anywhere for up to 6 weeks per year.
Professional Development: Additional paid leave for certifications and exams, with Agile-sponsored training programs for Microsoft and Databricks certifications.
Team Engagement: Enjoy regular team meetups, including state-based gatherings and an annual all-company event.
Equipment & Hardware: Receive an allowance for your home office setup and a 2-year equipment incentive.
Salary Packaging: Access novated leasing services for tax-effective car purchases.
Learning Resources: Expand your skills with access to our digital library and learning platforms.
Opportunity to work with some of the best developers in the business including one on one mentoring with senior consultants.

Why Agile Insights?

Work with some of the largest clients and global brands across diverse industries.
Be part of a fast-growing, award-winning team passionate about transforming organisations with Data & AI.
Thrive in a friendly start-up culture that values innovation, collaboration, and work-life balance.

Ready to Lead with Us?

If you’re passionate about analytics, consulting, and community engagement, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply now to join Agile Insights and take your career to the next level!

No Agencies - No overseas applications - Must be in Australia and have full work rights

Machine Learning & AI Engineer

DyFlex is an SAP Platinum Partner delivering high-quality SAP solutions across Australia. We’re now expanding our Data and AI practice to match the strength and reputation of our established SAP capability.

As a Machine Learning & AI Engineer, you’ll design, build, and deploy scalable data and machine learning solutions that deliver real business value. You’ll use strong SQL and modern cloud platforms to create reliable pipelines and support ML workloads. Experience with tools like Spark or Databricks is a plus but not required. You will work on meaningful technical challenges with autonomy and communicate technical outcomes clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

We value engineers who think creatively, communicate effectively, and engage confidently with stakeholders. We’re looking for engineers who do more than write code. You’ll listen to client challenges, dig into the core problem, help shape solutions, and explain them clearly. If you want to build something from the ground up with a team that’s already proven it can deliver meaningful outcomes, we’d like to hear from you.

Your tasks and responsibilities:

Build and maintain scalable data and machine learning pipelines for ingesting, transforming, and delivering data into production environments
Develop and maintain SQL-driven data models, reports, and analytical outputs that support real business use cases
Manage and optimise databases, data warehouses, and cloud storage solutions, including platforms such as Databricks, Snowflake, or cloud-native services
Implement data quality checks, validation processes, and testing to ensure reliable, production-ready systems
Design, build, and deploy cloud-based solutions across AWS, Azure, or GCP
Contribute to practical machine learning solutions, including feature engineering, model integration, and pipeline automation
Take ownership of clearly defined technical components, working independently while collaborating closely with senior engineers and stakeholders
Engage with internal teams and clients to understand business problems and translate them into workable technical solutions
Apply modern engineering best practices, including version control, CI/CD, and infrastructure as code

Your qualifications and experience:

Junior to intermediate hands-on experience in data engineering, analytics engineering, or machine learning-adjacent roles in production environments
Strong proficiency in SQL and Python, with the ability to write efficient queries, build pipelines, and support analytical and ML workflows
Experience working with modern data or processing frameworks such as Apache Spark, Airflow, dbt, Kafka, or similar tools
Practical exposure to machine learning pipelines, applied ML use cases, MLOps concepts, or agent-based / automated workflows is highly regarded
Solid understanding of relational databases, data modelling, and query optimisation
Experience working with cloud data platforms such as Databricks, Snowflake, or comparable technologies
Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Data Science, Mathematics, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience
Strong problem-solving mindset with the ability to work independently, adapt quickly, and approach problems creatively
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to clearly explain technical concepts to both technical and non-technical stakeholders

What we offer:

Work with SAP’s latest technologies on cloud as S/4HANA, BTP and Joule, plus Databricks, ML/AI tools and cloud platforms
A flexible and supportive work environment including work from home
Competitive remuneration and benefits including novated lease, birthday leave, remote working, additional purchased leave, and company-provided laptop
Competitive remuneration and benefits including novated lease, birthday leave, salary packaging, wellbeing programme, additional purchased leave, and company-provided laptop Comprehensive training budget and paid certifications (Databricks, SAP, cloud platforms)
Structured career advancement pathways with mentoring from senior engineers
Exposure to diverse industries and client environments

Join a renowned organisation delivering projects to some of Australia’s leading enterprises

DyFlex is committed to providing a safe, flexible and respectful environment for staff free from all forms of discrimination, bullying and harassment. We are proud of our diverse and inclusive team as only together we can continually improve ourselves and achieve best outcomes for our customers– we are the region's leading SAP Platinum Partner!

Please note that we cannot offer visa sponsorship for this role. Applicants must have full working rights in Australia.

·         Build and mature Dyno Nobel’s modern data platform

·         Drive data modelling, governance and analytics uplift across the business

·         Base Salary $150,000 + super + annual bonus




At Dyno Nobel Limited, our people vision is to unlock our people capability and culture to create safe, inclusive and high‑performing teams on the ground.




The Role

As IT Senior Analyst – Data Analytics, you will play a key role in developing, governing and enhancing Dyno Nobel’s modern data platform. This role partners closely with stakeholders across the organisation to deliver clear, governed and scalable data models and reporting solutions.

Working across Databricks, Denodo, SAP BW/BI and other enterprise data technologies, you will design and build data models, pipelines and reporting structures that enable better decision‑making and uplift data literacy across the business. You will also contribute to establishing governance frameworks and embedding new ways of working as Dyno Nobel advances its data maturity.




You will:

·         Design and develop conceptual, logical and physical data models aligned to architectural standards

·         Build and maintain ETL pipelines using Databricks and Azure toolsets

·         Integrate data from SAP, SQL and other enterprise systems into unified models

·         Support and enhance SAP BW/BI reporting solutions and related analytics

·         Apply data governance, metadata management and data lineage practices

·         Engage proactively with stakeholders to translate requirements and uplift data literacy

 

What you’ll bring

·         You must be committed to positively contributing to our safe, inclusive and high-performance culture.

·         Tertiary qualifications in Computer Science (or related discipline)

·         Experience across data platforms, including Databricks, data modelling and ETL pipeline development

·         Strong SAP BW/BI capability, including BO/BI4.X and Power BI development and support

·         Proven ability to translate business requirements into scalable, governed data products

·         Strong communication, facilitation and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to influence and uplift data literacy

·         Experience working in complex or global environments, with exposure to tools such as Denodo and KPI/scorecard frameworks




If you are excited about the role and think you have what it takes but your experience doesn’t align 100%, we still want to hear from you.




Benefits to you

 We are a team focused on safety, inclusion and high performance.




18 weeks paid parental leave for primary carer, 3 weeks for secondary carer

Superannuation paid on unpaid parental leave, up to 12 months

Hybrid work model

Salary packaging options

Confidential employee assistance program

Mental health and wellbeing program

Options to purchase annual leave (where eligible)

Various corporate discount programs

Workplace giving charitable scheme

Opportunities for career progression through succession planning and development reviews




Please be advised that our hybrid work model entails three office days and two remote workdays per week. This structure aims to enhance efficiency and teamwork, while upholding a harmonious work flexibility.

 About Us

 As an ASX100 company and industry front‑runner, Dyno Nobel Limited offers diverse career opportunities globally, emphasising safety, inclusivity and high performance. Our passionate team of almost 6,000 employees work across our global operations to manufacture and distribute industrial explosives and industrial chemicals.

 Leveraging diversity through inclusion

 At Dyno Nobel Limited, we believe in the strength of diversity and inclusivity, fostering an environment that is safe, equitable and embraces differences to enhance performance. We go beyond ‘diversity of thought’, valuing people from a variety of backgrounds and encouraging applicants from diverse identities.

Our commitment extends to helping our team excel at work while achieving a harmonious work‑life balance. To support this, we offer a range of work styles and a paid parental leave policy, ensuring our team thrives both personally and professionally.

 Apply now to be part of our inclusive and thriving community.

 What our employees say

 “Everyone has been very welcoming which has been lovely!”

 About our process

We value diversity, equity and inclusion and are committed to ensuring a welcoming experience for all candidates. We encourage you to share any support or adjustments you need to be at your best during our recruitment process. Senior Business Analyst – CRM Program
Contract: Until 30 June 2026 plus extension | Brisbane CBD | Hybrid working

We are seeking an experienced Senior Business Analyst to join a large-scale, enterprise CRM transformation within a major Queensland organisation. This is a critical role within a long-running, high-profile program that is preparing to go to market for CRM vendor selection (RFP), followed by implementation.

This opportunity will suit a pragmatic, adaptable Senior Business Analyst with strong CRM delivery experience who is comfortable operating across early-stage discovery, market engagement and downstream implementation activities.

The Program

This multi-year transformation is focused on modernising customer engagement and consolidating fragmented customer data into a single, enterprise CRM platform. The program spans technology, operations, finance, risk and people, and operates within a complex regulatory environment.

The CRM initiative will establish a foundational enterprise capability, balancing standard CRM functionality with a targeted level of organisation-specific configuration to support business needs and long-term scalability.

Key Responsibilities

Support CRM market engagement and RFP activities, including requirements definition, vendor clarification and evaluation support.

Work closely with business stakeholders to elicit, analyse and document functional and non-functional requirements.

Translate business needs into clear, fit-for-purpose CRM solution designs, aligned to platform capabilities and best practice.

Leverage prior CRM implementation experience to advise stakeholders on design options, trade-offs and effective usage of CRM tools.

Contribute to shaping how the organisation will consume, embed and adopt the CRM, balancing configuration versus customisation.

What we’re looking for

Strong Senior Business Analyst capability, with experience operating in large, complex programs of work.

Hands-on CRM implementation experience (product-agnostic; experience with tier-one CRM platforms highly regarded).

Demonstrated experience across end-to-end delivery, ideally including vendor-led implementations.

Ability to work effectively through ambiguity and early-stage definition, while maintaining structure and momentum.

Why apply through Lime Recruitment?

Enjoy two pay runs per week with no contractor fees. As a Queensland-owned agency, we offer personalised service and are a Tier 1 supplier to the Queensland Government. Awarded Australia’s top-performing small agency in 2021 and 2022, and finalist in 2023, Lime Recruitment partners with experienced, genuine recruiters focused on securing the right opportunities.

Looking for an exciting new challenge where your financial skills can really make a difference?

Our Commercial and People team is excited to be seeking a talented Senior Finance Analyst who loves turning numbers into insights and initiatives into member value.

You'll be part of a highly skilled, well-regarded Finance Team that supports critical initiatives and regulatory requirements. Day to day, you'll be the go to person for financial modelling, analysis, monitoring, reporting, and benefits realisation.

You will maintain a close working relationship with project managers, sponsors and other business stakeholders including Senior Leadership. It's a role where you can truly shape how projects are assessed, run, and measured — and ensure value is delivered to our members.

You'll touch work like:

Modelling and analysis to support regulatory and risk management compliance
Business partnering support to project and initiative stakeholders
Income projections, product cost allocation and industry benchmarking analysis
Value-to-member benefits realisation analysis

About you:

You'll have significant experience in financial modelling and project accounting in financial services, superannuation or a similar highly regulated environment. This is a critical role within our organisation so naturally your functional expertise is supported by outstanding communication and relationship building skills and an ability to provide timely, accurate, value add advice to a wide variety of stakeholders to support sound decision making.

You will have:

Intermediate to advanced Excel and financial modelling expertise.
Proven experience uplifting and maturing cross functional processes and procedures.
Strong communication skills to explain complex modelling and data analysis to diverse stakeholders, including the Executive Team.
Exceptional analytical and problem solving ability — turning complexity into clear decisions.
Ability to translate technical information for non technical audiences.

In addition, the following will be highly regarded:

Membership of CPA, CA ANZ, or a similar professional body.
Finance ERP experience (TechnologyOne is advantageous).

Apply now and join a team where your financial expertise directly contributes to delivering value for our members. Expect collaboration, continuous improvement, and strategic thinking — with plenty of opportunities to shape how projects are assessed, managed, and measured.

Benefits that matter and make a difference for our employees

Leave for those moments that matter, an additional 6 days of leave at the end of year, up to 6 days paid volunteer leave, gender neutral paid parental leave of 20 weeks, Gender Affirmation leave, reproductive health and wellbeing leave, Cultural and Ceremonial leave. Access your LSL after 3 years, take AL at half pay, and purchase up to 2 weeks additional leave (just to name a few!).
Your Professional development matters, up to $5k per year professional development and up to 8 days professional development leave, HESTA scholarships and free access to a range of premium learning tools.
Your health and wellbeing matters, free annual flu shots and skin checks, incredible social events throughout the year and a comprehensive employee assistance program available 24/7.
Your financial wellbeing matters, 15% super, financial planning support, end of year payment for all Enterprise Agreement-covered employees, incentivised Employee Referral Program and novated lease options.

Who we are

Paladin Energy is a global uranium producer with scale and growth. We have a multi-decade production and growth pipeline, operating in the world’s premier uranium jurisdictions – Namibia, Canada and Australia.

Our company is growing and this means there are great career opportunities for motivated individuals. By joining our team, you become part of Paladin’s next chapter. Dual-listed on the ASX and TSX, we are ramping up production at our Langer Heinrich Mine in Namibia and striving to expand our role as one of the world’s leading independent producers of uranium by developing the PLS Project in Canada

Our vision “Clean Energy. Clear Future” embodies our purpose to resource a global low-carbon future and contribute to the decarbonisation of many economies. You can be part of this exciting journey and make a difference to the future.

The Opportunity

Paladin is seeking a Data Analytics and AI Lead to drive business value by strategically leveraging data, information and artificial intelligence (AI) across our global operations.

This role will lead the transition from basic reporting to predictive, automated and insight-driven decision making, defining and delivering Paladin’s data, analytics and AI strategy and roadmap. A strong focus will be placed on governance, risk management, and maximising return on investment, including the Company’s investment in Microsoft Fabric.

To be successful in the role, the following is essential:

Tertiary qualifications in Information Technology, Commerce or a related field

Proven experience developing and delivering enterprise data, analytics and/or AI strategies aligned to business objectives

Strong understanding of data foundations, including data quality, governance, security, privacy and information management

Experience identifying and managing AI-related risks, including safety, privacy, IP and regulatory compliance

Capability to lead the selection, implementation and support of analytics and AI platforms and tools

Strong stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to influence, communicate insights and drive adoption to achieve business goals

A demonstrated commitment to Paladin’s core values of Integrity, Respect, Courage and Community in everything you do

A collaborative approach with a strong focus on safety, quality and continuous improvement

Hold valid Australian work rights

Hold, or be willing to obtain, a current National Police Clearance

Key Responsibilities

The key duties and accountabilities of this position include:

At Hazeldenes, we are proud of our people, our reputation, and our place in the community. From humble beginnings in Kangaroo Flat in Bendigo, our facilities have spread across rural Victoria. ABOUT THE ROLE

This role is well suited to a junior to early-career professional looking to build deep capability in procurement, commercial analysis and commodity markets within a large, well-established FMCG business.

Work closely with suppliers to ensure accurate data, reporting and compliance

Partner with Finance and Planning teams to support forecasting and budgeting 

Governance & Continuous Improvement

Ensure compliance with procurement policies, governance frameworks and audits

Maintain audit-ready documentation across contracts and transactions

Contribute to improvements in procurement systems, tools and reporting processes

 

 ABOUT YOU 

You are analytical, commercially minded and eager to learn. You enjoy working with numbers, contracts and market data, and you’re motivated to build a long-term career in procurement or agribusiness.

Qualifications & Experience

2–5 years’ experience in procurement, supply chain, finance or commercial analysis

Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Business, Agriculture, Economics, Supply Chain or similar

Understanding of financial reporting and working capital concepts 

Technical & Analytical Skills

Strong Excel and data analysis capability (Power BI desirable)

Experience supporting procurement processes, contracts or category management

Ability to translate data into practical commercial insights 

Work Style & Attributes

High attention to detail and strong analytical thinking

Deep experience in data governance or data management within a financial institution, with substantial experience in directly partnering with senior business stakeholders and operational teams to roll out data governance frameworks within an investments domain.

Experience with Investment data management tools like FactSet, BlackRock Aladdin, GoldenSource, SimCorp Dimension, IHS Markit, Matrix IDM.
Experience working with cross-functional teams in a project environment to deliver data governance solutions.
Excellent communication skills, capable of articulating complex data governance concepts to a diverse range of stakeholders and capable.
Relevant Tertiary qualifications.

Join us on our mission to make a better world of work. 

Culture Amp is the world’s leading employee experience platform, revolutionizing how 25 million employees across more than 6,500 companies create a better world of work. How you can help make a better world of work


We are seeking a Senior Product Manager to lead our Data Products portfolio within the Data Intelligence camp. Your mission will be to bring together the rich data between Culture Amp products and surface it in our new insights engine that will deliver to AI Coach, our AI-driven intelligence layer, and other new data product experiences. 

This will help our thousands of customers answer complex questions about workplace engagement, performance confidence, talent management, and organisational performance. 

In this role, you will lead two specialised groups: data engineers focused on data management for our insights engine, and data scientists responsible for maximising value from the rich data available for us to drive actionable insights for our customers. 

You will need to be technically conversant, but keep your focus firmly on the customer impact and commercial outcomes. 

What you’ll spend your time doing

Setting the direction: You’ll own the roadmap for our insights engine, enabling us to slice data optimally for product experiences and be delivered via methods such as APIs and MCP. This foundation will allow product teams to compute many insights on demand with the necessary high performance.
Leading data discovery: You will be close to our customers, partnering with data scientists, product managers, designers, and people scientists to identify what is viable and meaningful within our data before we build. This may include data profiling, statistical analysis, rapid prototyping, customer interviews, and/or market research to ensure our insights solve real-world problems.
Extending our benchmarks & statistical products: You will oversee our cornerstone survey benchmarks and the development of new statistical data products. 
Navigating complexity: Defining boundaries between domain concepts spanning customer & industry terminology, data modelling/schemas/specifications, authorisation models, and internal systems so as to make the product development process efficient and easy to navigate. 
Collaboration & communication: Serve as the point of contact for a range of technical and non-technical stakeholders. You will translate technical constraints into clear trade-offs and outcomes, creating artifacts that communicate both the 'why' and the 'what' of your team's work.
Product lifecycle & advocacy: You will evangelise our insights capabilities across the business, aligning multiple teams on a unified customer data and insights strategy while maintaining a balance of short term value and long term health.
What you’ll potentially bring to the table

Data roots: You probably have hands-on experience in a data-centric field such as analytics, data science, machine learning, or engineering. You are comfortable with the nitty-gritty of data modeling and appreciate the complexities of cloud-based data infrastructure. 
Commercial awareness: It would be Ideal if you had a proven track record of developing and launching data products to market. While this is not essential, you must be able to translate technical outputs into commercial value and enjoy the process of customer discovery to prioritisation to launch. You can measure success by how effectively your portfolio delivers commercial value for the business. 
AI familiarity: You should have an appreciation and some familiarity with use of Large Language Models and data constraints for AI product development.
Resilience & stakeholder management: You can handle the high expectations of a wide variety of stakeholders. You are comfortable making difficult trade-offs between future-state architecture and immediate feature delivery.
Balance of detail and strategy: You can manage highly detailed statistical decisions while maintaining the big picture vision required to motivate a cross-functional team of engineers and scientists.
Research and communication: You can collect qualitative and quantitative inputs to find patterns and distill them into actionable insights. You have a proven ability to explain complex technical concepts to diverse audiences.
Curiosity & passion: You are what we call a "people geek" - someone who is genuinely curious about the intersection of data, human behavior, and organisational culture.

We believe that our employees are the heartbeat of our success. We're committed to fostering a work environment that truly cares for and develops its people, and creates lasting positive impact. In addition to providing a competitive compensation package, some of the key benefits we offer are: 

Employee Share Options Program: We empower you to be an owner in Culture Amp and share in our success
Programs, coaching, and budgets to help you thrive personally and professionally
Access to external providers for mental wellbeing and coaching support to sustain the wellbeing, safety and development of our people
Monthly Camper Life Allowance: An automatic allowance paid out each month with your pay - you can spend it however you like to help improve your experience and life outside work
Team budgets dedicated to team building activities and connection
Intentional quarterly wellbeing pauses: A quarterly company-wide shutdown day in each region to to collectively pause, reset and focus on restoration and rest, without having to tap into individual vacation time
Extended year-end breaks: An extended refresh period at the end of year
Excellent parental leave and in work support program available from day 1 of joining Culture Amp
5 Social Impact Days a year to make a positive impact on the community outside of work
MacBooks for you to do your best & a work from home office budget to spend on setting up your home office
Medical insurance coverage for you and your family (Available for US & UK only) 

Additionally, we don't just focus on our internal community; we believe in creating a better world of work for all. We're committed to diversity, equity, and inclusion, with Employee Resource Groups and ally communities in place. 

We have a strong commitment to Anti-Racism, and endeavor to lead by example. Every step we make as a business towards anti-racism is another step we can take to support our customers in making a better world (of work). You can see our current commitments to Anti-Racism here.

Ad Text:
Lead and shape the future of responsible AI innovation
Collaborate effectively with diverse stakeholders by leveraging strong communication and partnering skills
Permanent, Full-time, Sydney CBD, Hybrid

Drive innovation in Data & AI—shape ethical solutions and deliver real impact with us!




ABOUT THE ROLE

Are you passionate about leveraging artificial intelligence to make a meaningful impact? We are seeking an experienced Senior Business Analyst who will play a critical role in triaging AI-related requests, supporting the AI Ethics and Advisory Committee, and leading cutting-edge AI experimentation initiatives. This dynamic position offers the opportunity to collaborate with talented colleagues, tackle complex challenges, and shape the future of responsible AI development.




Key responsibilities:

Collaborate and partner with a wide range of stakeholders to understand business needs, build strong relationships, and ensure alignment of AI initiatives with organisational goals.
Efficiently triage and prioritise AI requests from various stakeholders, ensuring timely and effective resolution.
Provide technical and strategic support to the AI Ethics and Advisory Committee, contributing to policy development and ethical decision-making.
Lead experimentation and pilot projects in AI and machine learning, driving innovation and continuous improvement.
Communicate complex technical concepts clearly to diverse audiences, fostering understanding and engagement.




ABOUT YOU

You possess the drive, passion, and determination to set your own vision and strive to make a meaningful impact. You will be partnering with a variety of stakeholders to build strong relationships and ensure alignment with organisational goals. You have a strong problem-solving mindset, excellent communication skills, and the ability to embrace challenges. Additionally, you are committed to upholding ethical standards in AI and promoting responsible innovation.  To be successful in this role you will also demonstrate:

5+ years driving impactful AI and IT projects as a Senior Business Analyst in dynamic, cross-functional teams
Leading or contributing to AI projects
Proficiency with Jira and Confluence
Exceptional written and verbal communication
Desired: Proficiency in SDLC, Test Development Lifecycle, and agile methodologies.

 

ABOUT US

Chartered Accountants Australia and New Zealand (CA ANZ) represents more than 140,000 financial professionals, supporting them to make a meaningful difference in the communities where they work and live. We are committed to advancing the profession through high ethical standards, world-class education, and advocacy for the public good. Guided by our purpose and values, we aspire to be a magnet for diverse talent, equip our members for success, and lead the way in sustainability, innovation, and trust in business and finance.




WHAT’S IN IT FOR YOU

At CA ANZ, we are committed to creating a workplace that reflects our values of collaboration, integrity, diversity, and accountability. As part of our strategy to be a magnet for diverse talent and an adaptive, member-centric organisation, we offer:




A strong focus on equity, diversity, and inclusion embedded in everything we do
Opportunities to grow your career through inspiring learning and development pathways
A flexible hybrid work model that balances autonomy with the benefits of in-person collaboration
A culture that values your voice and empowers you to make an impact in your community and profession
Grow your skills and future with unlimited access to LinkedIn learning
The chance to contribute to meaningful work that creates real impact for people across Aotearoa and Australia







HOW TO APPLY

Simply select APPLY NOW and submit your application today. Applications close Tuesday, 10 February 2026.




CA ANZ welcomes applications from people of all ages, genders, cultural and linguistic backgrounds, Māori, Pasifika, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people with a disability, and people who are diverse in gender and sexuality.

Deliver analytics that directly influence portfolio decisions and investment outcomes
Be recognised as a technical expert and mentor within a high‑calibre analytics team
12‑month maximum‑term opportunity with strong exposure to portfolio managers and senior stakeholders


Perpetual Group is an ASX-listed company (ASX:PPT) headquartered in Sydney, Australia, currently consisting of 11 leading brands across three distinct businesses: Asset Management, Wealth Management and Corporate Trust.

Perpetual Asset Management is a global multi-boutique asset management business offering an extensive range of specialist investment capabilities through seven boutiques and brands in key regions globally. Within Australia, Perpetual and Pendal have a broad range of capabilities across Australian and global equities, credit, fixed income, multi-asset and ESG. We have a growing presence in the US, UK and Europe through our brands Barrow Hanley, Trillium, JO Hambro, Regnan, and TSW.

About the role

As a Senior Analyst, Investment Analytics, you will play a critical role in delivering accurate, timely and insightful performance and attribution reporting across a broad range of asset classes. You'll provide technical oversight, act as a subject matter expert on complex attribution matters and support continuous improvement across the Investment Analytics function.

This 12-month max term contract role offers significant exposure to portfolio managers and senior stakeholders and is well suited to someone who enjoys combining technical expertise with collaboration, problem‑solving and mentoring.


Key Responsibilities:

Deliver daily and monthly performance and attribution reporting across equity, fixed income, diversified and absolute return strategies.
Provide daily fixed income and equity attribution analysis to portfolio managers, with clear and concise explanations.
Complete month‑end performance, attribution and ad‑hoc reporting requests.
Act as a subject matter expert on complex attribution queries and present insights to senior stakeholders.
Identify operational issues early and resolve or escalate appropriately.
Manage data flows across holdings, pricing, benchmarks, corporate actions and analytics outputs.
Work effectively with IBOR and ABOR data structures and custodial feeds.
Support BAU delivery through strong governance, controls and data quality processes.
Build risk knowledge to support cross‑training with the Investment Risk team.
Provide technical guidance and support to junior analysts.

What We're Looking For:

Degree qualification (preferred).
CFA and/or CIPM qualifications beneficial.
5+ years' experience in performance measurement or investment analytics.
Proven experience delivering performance and attribution reporting under time‑critical deadlines.
Strong understanding of fixed income performance drivers, including carry, roll‑down, duration, curve, spreads, FX and inflation‑linked analytics.
Ability to interpret and clearly explain analytics to portfolio managers and non‑technical stakeholders.
Advanced Excel, Power Query, Power BI and SQL skills.
Strong experience with FactSet performance and analytics modules.
Experience working with IBOR vs ABOR data and custodial feeds.
Exposure to investment risk frameworks desirable.
Demonstrated ability to leverage digital tools and emerging analytics capabilities to improve efficiency and insights.
Strong risk awareness and commitment to regulatory and internal governance standards.


How we work


Our unique culture is underpinned by our three organisational behaviours, Stretch, Own it, Make an impact which drive our approach of day-to-day interactions with colleagues and clients, the way we approach decision-making to the questions we ask and the problems we solve.


Employee benefits

Work from anywhere in Australia for up to one month each year
An annual allowance to empower you to prioritise your personal wellbeing
Study support and commitment to supporting professional development


Diversity and inclusion

Strong commitment to all aspects of Diversity and Inclusion through a robust 7 pillar strategy
A growing number of employee-led networks who work to raise awareness and drive continued change
We support over 50 First Nations Communities, helping to secure the communities' future. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People


We're committed to creating an inclusive workplace where diversity is celebrated. No matter your background or circumstances, we aim to provide an environment where you can thrive.

Work type: Permanent / Full time
Location: Support Office - Docklands


From humble beginnings in downtown Bendigo to supporting Australian communities far and wide- Myer has always been a special place, transcending beyond just a place to work.

Myer is a place for finding life-long friendships, a safe space with a big heart. Here, you’re encouraged to be yourself, share your ideas and are entrusted to deliver your very best. Some might even say it feels like being “right at home”.

MYER is looking for an Insights Business Partner who will play a critical role in transforming how Myer leverages data and insights to drive strategic decisions. This role acts as a trusted advisor and partner to stakeholders in Myer’s Merchandise business unit providing actionable insights to inform decision-making and enhance engagement, performance, and growth with our customers and our suppliers.

Combining technical expertise with a deep understanding of retail dynamics, the role requires a strategic mindset, analytical proficiency, and the ability to translate complex data into clear, actionable recommendations to support the Full Potential Plan, Insight Led Buying and Marketing Optimisation Analyses. Success in this role requires a balance of tactical execution and visionary leadership, including a willingness to roll up your sleeves, lead a team of specialists, and contribute meaningfully to organizational strategy.

Exciting new opportunity in our Loyalty and Content department
Join our growing MYER team
Flexible hybrid working model – mix of working in our Docklands Support Office and Work-From-Home

 About the role:

Build strong, collaborative relationships with stakeholders across assigned business functions.
Act as the primary point of contact for insights and analytics support, ensuring alignment with strategic objectives.
Partner with stakeholders to embed data and insights into decision-making processes.
Develop and deliver data-driven insights tailored to business needs, focusing on areas such as category performance, customer behaviour, marketing effectiveness, and operational efficiencies.
Translate data into actionable strategies to drive growth, incremental revenue growth, improve profitability, and enhance customer experiences.
Adopt common standards and best practices for how insight projects are initiated, prioritised, developed and delivered, including following organisational guidelines for data privacy and security
Curate, present, and disseminate actionable insights and strategic recommendations to internal and external stakeholders, including senior leadership and C-Suite executives
Conduct deep dives into customer behaviour, market trends, and competitive analysis to uncover opportunities and risks.
Support the development of segmentation strategies to guide differentiated approaches to win in the market
Guide and oversee the development and usage of reporting and dashboards that provide access for the team and stakeholders to regular performance & customer insights.
Identify opportunities for new Insight capabilities and enhancements and guide and lead their development
Lead insight enhancement projects and deliver deep-dive analyses to address key business challenges and drive data-led decisions.

About you:

Demonstrated expertise in a senior insights role within a fast-paced consumer environment (e.g., FMCG or Retail).
An impactful storyteller with a knack for identifying the “so what” from complex data
Proven track record of leading and developing high-performing insight and analytics teams.
Demonstrated success in partnering with cross-functional teams and influencing strategic decisions through data.
Proven ability to manage multiple projects and deliver results in a fast-paced environment.
Demonstrated success in fostering collaborative relationships with a diverse range of stakeholders.
Experience in managing and influencing senior stakeholders to drive strategic change and achieve unified consensus.
Extensive experience in change management, introducing new concepts, and leading stakeholders through transformation journeys.
Background in building and instilling a culture of ownership, collaboration, and innovation within teams.

Benefits to you:

Generous team member discounts on all Myer products, including team-member exclusive discounts.
Access to lifestyle leave and volunteer leave – arrange work around your life, not life around work.
A supportive leadership and team network to set you up for success.
Career growth and succession opportunities across the business.

Here, you’re not only an employee. You’re a valued Team Member with real dreams that we want to help you chase, no matter how big or small. At Myer, we’re all about making your work life meaningful. We want you to experience life’s special moments fully, which is why we take pride in offering balance and flexible options to get you to where you want to be.

Wherever you are and wherever you’re going, we’ll meet you there and get you to your destination. With your enthusiasm and our support, we’re fully committed to helping you thrive and flourish. The future lies in your hands.

Welcome Home!

As our highly valued Manager, Credit Risk Analytics based in Brisbane you will bring your strong analytical skills to support the Senior Manager, Credit Strategy, to execute the credit risk optimisation strategy for Great Southern Bank.

Working with key partners and internal stakeholders, you will pro-actively manage critical quantitative models and tools used in the origination and management of the bank's retail lending products (Home Loans, Credit Cards and Personal Loans) in a way that balances growth, customer experience and credit risk.

You'll make an impact by:

Leadership

You are accountable in supporting the development of a credit risk strategy that supports the bank's strategic objectives across its key portfolios and customer segments and assisting in the articulation of that strategy with senior leaders, executives, directors and regulators.
You will provide thought leadership across teams including Risk, Products, Projects and Data to influence effective design and delivery of leading loan origination pathways.

Credit Risk

In conjunction with the Senior Manager, Credit Strategy, you will design automated decisioning acquisition strategies and models to support existing and new products.
Using robust credit risk management techniques you will ensure the credit risk models and tools are designed in line with our Model Risk framework including appropriate monitoring and review that drives continuous improvement. This will include monitoring outcomes and performance, application of quantitative techniques, professional credit risk judgement, engagement with internal senior stakeholders and external partners, forums and regulators.
You will maintain and monitor the data and reporting for our credit risk tools and provide succinct summaries to the executive and credit committees. You will thrive for continuous improvement across credit risk models, tools and practices.
You will leverage your colleagues in the Credit Risk team, supporting each other with insights and professional opinions to drive outcomes across credit oversight, policy and loan decisioning tools.

Reporting, Analysis and Insights

You will develop and design regular reporting and analysis relating to application trends, new originations, and portfolio.
You will design and deliver reporting and insights that helps ensure the Board is able to fulfil its obligations for oversight of the lending portfolios.
You will support recurring and ad hoc quantitative analysis to ensure portfolio health is understood and to identify opportunities to better manage risk-return.
You may be required to support ongoing management of the provision model, including reporting as well reviewing and validating the model remains fit for purpose.
You may be required to conduct portfolio stress testing to further support credit insights and to contribute to enterprise stress testing and ICAAP.

Systems and partners

You will have dual responsibility for the execution and risk management of credit risk strategy, including design, business requirements, test planning and execution, model governance, data requirements etc.
You will work closely with technology platform owners and business owners to prioritise delivery of credit risk solutions into those platforms.

Partners and stakeholders

You will work the Senior Manager, Credit Strategy, Product Managers, Data and Technology partners and the management of our key external risk partners including but not limited to mortgage insurance, credit bureaux, valuation and scorecard providers and validators.



Do things differently with us

To succeed in this role, you will have:

5+ years' experience in credit risk management roles within Financial Services
Strong understanding of commonly used credit tools and decision engines and how to create the best value through their use
Proficient with data extraction, manipulation, and analysis (DataBricks and or SQL is essential).
Strong communication and stakeholder management skills
Familiarity with the Australian market, regulations (APRA, ASIC, AFCA)

Why Great Southern Bank?

Whatever your role with us, you'll be part of a force for good. We're owned by our customers right here in Australia, so our success benefits everyday people and families. Working at Great Southern Bank, you'll also enjoy a range of fantastic benefits, some examples include:

Helping you unlock a brighter future by investing in your development and wellbeing, offering you study leave, a day for you and professional wellbeing coaching.
Benefits that support you and your wellbeing so that you can thrive at work and at home, today and tomorrow. Enjoy access to our wellbeing centre and the flexibility to work from home two days a week.
Helping you to achieve your financial goals and positively impact your family and community. We offer discounts on a wide range of Great Southern Bank products and services such as savings and transaction accounts, insurance, home loans and more!

Imagine working for a bank that truly helps people. You can.

Our people bring energy and initiative to a fast-changing environment, making thoughtful decisions that balance doing good for our customers with driving sustainable success for our business. If you enjoy working in a place where priorities evolve, ideas are valued, and every action contributes to something bigger, you'll feel right at home here at Great Southern Bank.

We're looking for a Senior Analyst to join a Financial Crime Detection & Reporting team within a large financial services organisation. This role is heavily hands-on and technically focused, with a strong emphasis on advanced SAS programming to support financial crime detection, regulatory reporting, and data quality monitoring.

This is very much a data-heavy role - around 90% focused on data extraction, transformation, validation, and analysis, with a smaller component dedicated to reporting and visualisation.

Key Responsibilities

Develop and maintain advanced SAS programs to extract, transform, and analyse large and complex datasets

Support financial crime detection and regulatory reporting through robust data analytics and monitoring controls

Design and implement automated routines to assess data completeness, accuracy, and timeliness

Handle complex analytical queries across multiple source systems and data feeds

Produce clear, stakeholder-ready reporting, using Power BI for dashboards and visual outputs

Support and enhance existing analytics systems and controls

Job description:


Be part of a team that develops, deploys, supports, and modernises a proprietary business critical system.

Join a collaborative group that values curiosity, problem solving, and thoughtful engineering



The opportunity to join our team

We are looking for a Senior Analyst Engineer who enjoys solving complex problems, thrives in environments with uncertainty, and is ready for a new challenge. This team owns a proprietary system that is central to the business, and we are responsible for its end-to-end development, ongoing support, and continuous modernisation. A major focus over the coming period is a significant redevelopment of this system. This work involves architectural redesign, complex problem solving, and deep C++ engineering.

In this role you will work across development, production support, testing, and broader IT tasks, with the balance of work evolving over time based on system needs and team priorities. Flexibility, openness, and curiosity are key.

This is a great opportunity for someone who wants to apply their senior level software engineering expertise, contribute to a major area of system development, and play an influential role within a highly collaborative team.

What you will be doing
In this role you will work across a mix of development, support, and system improvement activities, contributing to both day to day outcomes and longer term engineering uplift.

Designing, developing, and delivering changes to business-critical systems using C++ and modern software design principles
Playing a central role in the upcoming system redevelopment, including rearchitecting components and solving complex technical challenges
Working closely with architects, delivery leads, technical specialists, and business partners to shape and implement quality solutions
Supporting production environments on a rotating roster to maintain system reliability and availability
Building deep knowledge of the unit pricing system and its broader ecosystem
Uplifting system capability and engineering practices across the team
Providing informal mentoring by sharing your technical strengths, explaining your reasoning clearly, and influencing decision making in positive ways
Helping shape a constructive, energetic, and supportive team culture

What You Bring to This Role
We are looking for someone who brings strong engineering capability, a positive mindset, and the confidence to operate in evolving and sometimes uncertain technical environments.

Strong C++ software development experience (ideally 8 or more years, but we are flexible for the right capability)
Strong software design skills and experience working in complex systems
Comfortable operating in technical ambiguity and taking ownership in uncertain situations
Someone who wants variety in their work and is open to the mix of responsibilities evolving over time
A proactive approach to problem solving with the ability to work independently when required
Clear communication skills and the ability to explain technical decisions in a way that helps others learn
A positive influence who brings energy, patience, and a willingness to help the team grow
Experience across cloud environments, DevOps practices, Linux, SQL, or scripting is beneficial but not required

Industry background is open. What matters most is your engineering capability, your mindset, and your appetite for challenge.

Find the better way

What gets us excited about working here? Helping people feel good about their money as one of Australia's leading financial wellbeing organisations. From those starting out to those retiring. As your team, we'll show up for you and together we will create financial wellbeing for every Australian. Because we know people who are confident about their financial future live better lives.

If this sounds like your kind of career, you sound like our kind of person. With us, you'll do work that builds your technical know-how and challenges our entire industry to move forward.
